cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO 

This paper deals with semantic segmentation on video, which is a computer vision task, hence it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The paper also proposes a new feature propagation scheme and a novel feature estimation scheme, which involve machine learning techniques, making it relevant to the cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper addresses the issue of inference speed, which is related to optimization and efficiency, making it relevant to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with video processing, which is related to robotics and automation, making it relevant to the cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category.
